      "id": "ai-lab-secure-rag--search",
      "page": "ai-lab/secure-rag/index.html",
      "page_title": "Secure RAG prototype",
      "anchor": "search",
      "title": "Ask the index about Philip's systems.",
      "text": "Retrieval console Every query runs through the same visible pipeline: parse, guardrail check, retrieve, rank, claim-safety labeling, render. Unsafe queries get refused. Weak queries get honest empty states — never invented answers. Results can only point to whitelisted public pages and generated public chunks. If the answer is not in that boundary, the demo returns a refusal, no-result, or planned-state label instead of inventing proof. Parse queryidle Guardrail checkidle Retrieve candidatesidle Rank + scoreidle Claim-safety labelsidle Render resultsidle No query yet. Run a suggested query or type your own. Results are ranked from the public-content index with a relevance score, matched keywords, and a claim-safety label. No queries logged this session yet. Persistent, reviewable audit logs are a planned control — this preview shows the shape.",
