      "page": "ai-lab/secure-rag/index.html",
      "page_title": "Secure RAG prototype",
      "anchor": "prototype-production",
      "title": "What can be claimed today, and what cannot.",
      "text": "Prototype vs production This panel is here to keep the portfolio honest. The demo proves product, architecture, security, and QA thinking; it does not claim a production RAG backend, private-data search, or measured semantic-retrieval quality. Clickable Secure RAG demo route on the public site. Local search, ranking, result cards, source links, and guardrail states. In-browser regression eval harness for guardrails, rankings, and honesty states. Site-wide secure /api/chat pattern for the separate AI assistant. Release checks: mobile QA, link crawl, syntax checks, and secret scans. Retrieval runs against the generated structured public corpus, loaded into browser memory. Ranking is keyword scoring, not semantic embeddings. Audit logs are a session-only preview, not persistent compliance logs. Refusals model the intended product behavior before real data is involved. Server-side ingestion pipeline with explicit corpus approval. Embedding privacy review, vector database, access control, and route-level auth. Answer synthesis with citations, source-boundary enforcement, and regression tests. Monitoring for latency, cost, fallback rate, refusals, and retrieval quality. Not a production vector database. Not private document search. Not a production compliance or private-data security system. Not measured semantic retrieval accuracy.",
