      "text": "The template Every case study covers the same ground, in the same order: Problem — what the project needed to prove or solve. What I built — the shipped feature set, without inflation. System design — the pipeline, with each stage labeled Live, Prototype, or Planned. Security & claim-safety decisions — what the system refuses to do, and why. QA evidence — the actual pre-release results, including what was caught and what was not covered. Lessons — what carries into the next build. Resume bullets & interview talking points — honest, specific, checkable against the live demo. Next-version roadmap — labeled planned until it ships.",
