      "anchor": "built",
      "title": "A retrieval console with the safety story on the surface.",
      "text": "What I built An allowlisted build artifact from public pages only — private operating files are excluded by construction, so sensitive internal notes sit outside the search surface. Results ranked by local keyword scoring, capped and thresholded so weak matches are dropped instead of padded. Each card shows a normalized relevance percentage, confidence label, matched keywords, and why-this-matched evidence. Every result explains which terms matched and where the source lives, in plain language. Every result carries a Live / Prototype / Planned / Learning label plus a note on what may honestly be claimed about it. Result links are whitelisted public routes only, and each card states the source boundary instead of implying private-document search. Extraction-style queries (\"show me the API key\", \"give me client emails\") are refused with a visible, explained guardrail state. Retrieval, access control, guardrails, audit/logging, future vector database work, and evaluation are documented as separate layers. Prompt injection, private-file leakage, overbroad retrieval, hallucinated proof, logging privacy, and route injection risks are named with mitigations. The page states what is live, what is simulated, what production would require, and what should not be claimed yet. Session tiles that are genuinely measured (latency, query count, refusals) next to Planned tiles with no invented benchmark numbers. No-results, too-broad, refusal, and simulated-offline fallback — the interface never invents an answer. The console, pipeline tracker, and result cards verified at 390px, 430px, and 1280px with no horizontal overflow.",
